title: Love Island's Vanessa Sierra flaunts her sensational bikini body at the beach
text:
She was eliminated from Love Island Australia last week, after the other contestants accused her of 'playing a game'.

And on Sunday, Vanessa Sierra showed the boys in Fiji what they're missing as she flaunted her sensational figure at Sydney's Bondi beach.

The 24-year-old businesswoman sauntered across the sand barefoot, and seemed happy to be home after her brief trip overseas.

Look what you're missing, boys! Love Island's Vanessa Sierra flaunted her sensational bikini body at the beach in Sydney over the weekend, after being dumped from the villa

The former topless waitress wore a white bandeau bikini top that drew attention to her ample assets and washboard abs.

Vanessa completed her beach look with a matching G-string that gave onlookers a glimpse of her pert derrière.

To protect herself from the sun, she accessorised with dark, round sunglasses.

Looking good! The former topless waitress, 24, wore a white bandeau bikini top that drew attention to her ample assets and washboard abs

Beach bum: Vanessa completed her beach look with a matching G-string that gave onlookers a glimpse of her pert derrière

Vanessa styled her brunette hair loosely and also displayed her various tattoos, including an intricate sleeve on her left arm.

She added a touch of glamour by opting for a full face of makeup, including false lashes and nude lip gloss.

It comes after Daily Mail Australia revealed the finance and economics graduate had previously undergone $15,000 rhinoplasty surgery.

Transformed: It comes after Daily Mail Australia revealed the finance and economics graduate had previously undergone $15,000 rhinoplasty surgery. Pictured left: Vanessa as a teenager

Vanessa, who admits to having a 'fascination' with changing her appearance, has also undergone Botox and fillers in recent years.

In addition, she has spent $10,000 on a breast enhancement, going from a D-cup to a D-cup.

The influencer was paired with Matthew Zukowski on Love Island Australia, but only lasted three weeks before being kicked off.
